  <summary>4/17/1997--Introduced.
Farmer Estate Tax Relief Act of 1997 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to exclude from the gross value of an estate, for purposes of the estate tax, specified portions of the value of a qualified family-owned farm business. Provides for a limited (the lesser of certain qualified medical expenses or $500,000) one-time exclusion from gross income of the gain from the sale or exchange of certain qualified family-owned farm interests.</summary>
